MANY people in Ximawusa village outside Giyani in Limpopo were left homeless after heavy storms destroyed houses over the weekend. The damage comes just after two other communities around Malamulele and Muyexe outside Giyani, were also hard hit by the storm in recent weeks. Mopani District Municipality spokesperson Witnes Tiva said the Municipality is still doing an assessment to find out how many people are affected and how the Municipality can assist. The affected villagers are Sawulani, Rotterdam, Mbawula Ximawusa and also part of Ba-Phalaborwa Municipality.